TASK_DESCRIPTION=The on-pre-tool-use.sh hook blocks Boss from using the Read tool on ANY file, including images/screenshots saved in task-attachments. Boss needs to be able to read images (screenshots from users) to understand visual issues before dispatching tasks. The hook should allow Boss to read files in .doey/tasks/task-attachments/ and /tmp/doey/ paths, while still blocking source code access.
TASK_SUBTASKS=1:Dispatched to Subtaskmaster 3.0 — add Boss Read exceptions to on-pre-tool-use.sh:done\n2:W3.1: Research Boss Read blocking logic in on-pre-tool-use.sh — find exact lines, understand exception pattern, report:done\n3:W3.2: Implement Boss Read exceptions in on-pre-tool-use.sh — allow image files and task attachments:done\n4:Review Gate: Sent to Task Reviewer (1.1):done\n5:Deployment: Sent to Deployment (1.2) after review PASS:pending
